""""Cerro Amboro (Rio Isama)""""--During this trip I climbed up the Rio Isama to the summit of Cerro Amboro in Parque Nacional de Amboro. As the trail is not established and winds over ridges and dense forest I have little idea of the exact locality. Nevertheless today I collected along the Rio Isama where the trail begins to the summit, near a sort of tunnel like canyon along the river. 60 km W. of Santa Cruz. Riverine forest in deep canyon

""""Cerro Amboro""""--During this trip I climbed up the Rio Isama to the summit of Cerro Amboro in Parque Nacional de Amboro. As the trail is not established and winds over ridges and dense forest I have little idea of the exact locality. Nevertheless today I collected between 1150-1300 m between the camp used to reach the summit and the grasslands about 2 km N. of the summit. 60 km W. of Santa Cruz. A number of habitats collected: Tangled Clusia woodlands 1050-1200 m, Ericaceous-Clusia scrub 1150-1200 m, grasslands 1150-1300 m

""""Cerro Amboro""""--During this trip I climbed up the Rio Isama to the summit of Cerro Amboro in Parque Nacional de Amboro. As the trail is not established and winds over ridges and dense forest I have little idea of the exact locality. Nevertheless today I collected between 1170 m and the summit at 1510 m. 60 km W. of Santa Cruz. A number of habitats collected: Tangled Clusia woodlands 1050-1200 m, Ericaceous-Clusia scrub 1170-1510 m, upper riverine woodlands 1250 m, grasslands cliffs 1300-1510 m. First botanical expedition to the actual summit

""""Cerro Amboro""""--During this trip I climbed up the Rio Isama to the summit of Cerro Amboro in Parque Nacional de Amboro. As the trail is not established and winds over ridges and dense forest I have little idea of the exact locality. Nevertheless today I collected between 900-1150 m between the camp used to reach the summit and the edge of the grasslands about 3 km E. of the summit. 60 km W of Santa Cruz. A number of habitats collected: Loma forest at 900-950 m, Woodland tangled with bamboo 950-1050 m, tangled Clusia woodland 1050-1200 m, Ericaceous-Clusia scrub 1150-1200 m, upper riverine woodlands 1150 m

Guapiacu, Trilha Verde. Palmeira cespitosa, 2m de altura, 1,5cm DAS. Folhas jovens vermelhas, bainha ca. 6cm compr., peciolo ca. de 16cm, raque ca. de 32cm compr., laminas inteiras, levemente discolores. Infrutescencia nao ramificada, pedunculo creme na base passando a vermelho no apice, ca. de 30cm compr., coberto por lanugem castanha, raque vermelha, ca. de 20cm compr., frutos imaturos verdes. Reserva Ecologica de Guapiacu

Guapiacu, Trilha Verde. Palmeira solitaria, 1,5m alt., 4cm DAS. Bainha foliar 22cm compr., peciolo 67cm compr., raque 64-69cm compr., lamina dividida uniformemente, ca. De 24 segmentos de cada lado da rque, 2,3-2,4cm x 42-44cm. Espata verde e lisa na inflorescencia, passando a estraminea quando em fruto, ca. 25cm compr., pedunculo verde na inflorescencia passando a vermelho-escuro quando em fruto; raque no mesmo padrao de coloracao do pedunculo, 15cm compr., raquilas vermelho-escuras, 1a e 2a ordem, 15-18cm compr, ca. de 13 raquilas. Frutos maduros pretos. Reserva Ecologica de Guapiacu

Reserva Florestal da Cia. Vale do Rio Doce. Arvore com cerca de 10-15m. Tronco com casca levemente rugosa com pequenas fissuras, de coloracao alboacinzentada. Frutoa amarelos quando maduros e ferrugineo-tomentoso quando passados. Semente com testa alva e arilo alaranjado muito carnoso e adocicado. Frutos saindo de ramos grossos(Caulifloria) e pendentes. Frutos com descencia tardia. Fotografias e frutos para a carpoteca e madeira, muito frequente nas matas. Reserva Natural Vale do Rio Doce (Particular)
